text: From the outside looking in, the cafe looks rather…intimate. Definitely one of the grandest looking ones in Saigon. I immediately went in to try out their famous Vietnamese coffee because every supermarket here is selling their famed coffee beans. First up, the salted coffee. Not the best tasting one but it would suffice. Second, the banana honey crepe. Not fantastic but it was unique in a sense. Would I come back here again? Not sure. But if I’m in a group, this would be the perfect setting for a get together for Vietnamese coffee for first timers.

Came here one morning to get a coconut coffee to go and was surprised with the flavour of the coffee. The coconut coffee tastes more like a coconut dessert than necessarily a coffee, yet not in a bad way. There could have been a little more coffee in the drink since it was primarily iced coconut. (Sweetness of the coffee can be altered to liking) Service is kind, speaks good enough English to have a small conversation and they have a good system in place in regards to the orders. I got my coffee to go and it came with everything you would need or want it to come. The coconut shavings were nice, yet something that for me it could have gone without. The cafe had a water/tea station where you could also get your selve serve items too. Overall a good experience and would try this cafe and their coffee again.
A cozy cafe consistent with the look and feel of other outlets. The fruit flavoured drinks can be on the sweeter side however.
More upscale cafe. Higher price than other cafes but nice seating inside and professional staff. 5 service. Coffee was well made: did not try any food

To start off with, the Vietnamese drip coffee here is good, nice, aromatic and strong. The food quality is not too bad too, I tried their banana crepes dessert (Banh Chuoi Mat Ong) which included chopped slices of ginger which I thought was unique. Honey on top was nice. Sadly, the service received from their many staff in store was poor. They had forgotten about my dessert order which I waited for a good 25 minutes after several reminders. The staff seem busy with their own matters as the shop wasn’t very busy. Atmosphere is nice, with nice music and plenty of seating space. Nice ambience to relax and enjoy.

Have a nice breakfast with a soft music ambience while looking at the hustle and bustle on the street. Tucked at the corner, I enjoyed my breakfast while viewing the busy life of Ho Chi Minh city. They serve a variety of food and drinks to choose from. Service is very helpful but I feel they need to improve because they spill some drinks when serving. The ambience is so relaxing. The price is a bit steep but I don't mind with good food, service and environment.
The worst egg coffee I had in Vietnam… I doubt if there was egg. I guess you should come here for the ambiance or to buy coffee beens… Not to Drink… Not Egg Coffee for Sure..

Nice coffee but extremely expensive. The egg coffee was a unique taste but you can get it cheaper somewhere else. We ordered 2 food but the arrival was way off for both. 1 came first n the other one only arrived 15 mins later.
Beautiful airy interior, air con, good menu choice, go for the pork, rice and fried egg - iced drinks are good here
A well-decorated cafe on a busy street corner with many cars and motorbikes cross-crossing each other. A nice place to see to the world go by. The staff is friendly and attentive.
Great coffee shop with nice view to the streets. Original VNese taste or western taste are served. Lunch meals are also available.
Lovely local coffee shop. Prices are reasonable and the coffee is locally grown so very awesome experience they also sell coffee inside

Nicer than Highland coffee. Came 6 years ago and was trying to seach for this cafe, they did a rebranding. Coffee was inconsistent over the days. Sometimes good sometimes meh.... Food is good. One of the raw cafe that serve hot food and beverages. Most cafe serve only drinks.

I saw the store’s promotional paper cup on a Vietnam Airlines flight, so I thought to give it a try. The place was quaint, borrowing a concept of East meets Western. Unfortunately, the coffee was underwhelming for my taste, especially since the brand carries the “number one” slogan. The beans I chose had a strong cocoa flavor—which I appreciated a lot—yet it didn’t spark anything special.

Not so easy to find the traditional drip coffee these days in HCM. Found this cafe that serves a wide variety and their special, Legend coffee. Had problems ordering because it was so confusing with the intensity etc. Im sure the beans are different from the usual even the presentation as well. BUT found it too acidic for my liking. Not much flavours or roast to it. AND it’s very expensive for a coffee, it was 150000 vnd.

If love vietnamese coffee, you will definitely love this place. It's quite famous and the have a wide variety of coffee from different origin, blends and grounds. Try the premium on, it's a bit expensive but you can truly have an excellent coffee experience. They sell turkish coffee nespresso machine capsules but I don't really recommend it. Focus on vietnamese choices, way better.
Nice relaxing chill place to enjoy a very tasty coffee. Service is top of it's class. Always a good crowd but not over crowded. Not too noisy because of the design.
Delicious coffee, a little bit more expensive than other places but really worth it! Friendly staff and nice interior with AC.
Good drinks, spacious and clean

Legends is a very famous cafe in saigon especially with vietnamese I tried here It is a high end luxurious cafe Coffee was delicious but not a wow Famous saigon bread was tasty but again not a wow But as i said it is kind of high end luxirious cafe You can smoke indoor Second floor has the hole street view It is a busy place And prices are really high compared to vietnam prices. Coffe was around 2.5 dollars.
Love love live the egg coffee! Good place to have your quick work here.

Good coffee. Place is cozy and will make you feel relaxed if you are tired of the busy streets. The moment you open the door the aroma of the coffee will warmly welcome you. I can stay all day here actually. :)
the staff here was very very kind. She tried to help me to buy vietnam traditional sweets:) even if this is not her business. I strongly recommend the coconut coffee set! it tastes nice😋
Came for the “legendary” Vietnamese coffee experience, saw a menu of weirdly pretentious names for coffee. Pure percolated rocket fuel is what it is.
Great decor. Comfortable. And good strong coffee.

I ordered a yogurt with fruit. The staff laughed at me I think and then gave me a cup 80% filled with ice and a tiny bit of fruit. No yogurt first time. I paid 70,000 for a cup of ice. Second time I talked to them it was just mixed with a spoon. Third time they used the blender. The final product was okay but it shouldn't have been that difficult. They apologized twice so at least they care.
Nice seating area, good service and good coffee. However the latte (no picture) was too weak. Quite expensive for Vietnamese standards. +free cold herbal tea(?) when you order something.

I'm disappointed with this store for 3 things: 1. Quality: I got Coffee No.4 with ice and milk, but the quality is not as good as in other branch (the best No.4 I've had is at Cong Hoa's branch). I asked for a bit more condensed milk and the staff added too much, and thus the coffee is not that good anymore. 2. The staff was quite inattentive: in other cafes, I find waiters and waitresses going around and serve water/ tea to customers. It would be nicer if Trung Nguyen can do it too (their staff just linger around the store though). At the counter, employees laugh and talk really loud. I was wondering if there's a store supervisor around. 3. The worst thing about this store is the music. Staff plays a Youtube list and there're just soooo many ads. They play all types of instrumental music, unlike in other brands where they play classical music. Sometimes, there's no music for hours, and then dance music (of course with no words as of the protocol). For such a big national chain, I expect them to standardize their playlist (and no ads). Besides, the place is really noisy in the afternoon (since people meet up for business I guess). If you are looking for a nice cafe to sit down and read a book in the afternoon, just don't come here at that time. I sat at a table near the kitchen and the oily food odor lingers around, so I gotta move. In the evening, it's more peaceful when there are not that many people. Definitely not coming back here again.
Classic Coffee Shop and warm surroundings.
smells like smoking and drinks take a long time to come but the ice cream is impressive and tatsy like a cake

A cafe by any other name, slick and well presented, always busy. Pretty good coffee. I was here once with my friends and one morning alone. The morning alone I asked for a Banh Mi but was told they had none, then I asked for some plain bread; also told they had none - was disappointing that all the bread on display was actually fake. To be fair if you like Green tea matcha great; but you are sadly disappointed if you want real dough.
Terrible value. Portions were small. Wouldn’t even bring food menu to table for you. Lots of items not available. Agree with what one review says, overpriced for air cond.

it’s tasted the same every time when I back in VN. price maybe almost the same to Starbucks which just a few block away from there, but way much far better than… delicious, glamorous, fascinating! 👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻
Very nice coffee shop in the city center. Some good foods for lunch sound good.

The coffee tastes definitely great. Order your coffee with condensed milk, and make sure it's a nice arabica-robusta blend. It's not just the aroma, the texture of the coffee here is definitely on point too. The vibe is very chill and everyone is just having a relaxing afternoon in the middle of the busy Saigon and hiding from the extreme heat.
Nice place for coffee. Coffee size a bit small. Less than half a cup without the massive amount of ice. WiFi available.

Great coffee spot, which was also convenient to my accommodation (8 min walk). They have the standard variety of hot and cold drinks (coffee, teas). Highly recommend an egg coffee and croissant. Staff are friendly and helpful, also helped me when I accidentally ordered my Grab to a wrong address woops.

Deliciously smooth, chocolatey coffee - had the creative 3, although was encouraged quite well by waitress to order the creative 8, but did not want the increased caffeine late at night. Apparently, 8 is the artificial weasel coffee here, will have to try next time.

I stopped by in the morning and ordered an egg coffee for 86,000 VND but the quality was just mediocre. The coffee didn’t taste good at all and it took forever for the staff to make. I then stopped by in the evening to buy some gifts for my friends. I was looking at the pre-packaged products on the shelves and one of the employees kept following me around. I did not feel comfortable because I was trying to decide which one to buy and I kept getting interrupted by the employee. I wasn’t there to steal and you guys have camera so just calm the hell down.
Nice ambience Tried the Signature Legend Coffee & Vietnam Egg Coffee both are good!

I ordered watermelon juice without ice and sugar then they asked me for 68k and the price was 59k in menu. They said special juice. I waited then saw 100ml of juice and the juice was only red color without real taste of watermelon. I thought a special watermelon juice will taste good and they may use a good quality of watermelon. But very worse juice. Sorry but it was a bad experience in 10 years.
Tasty coffee and stylish environment. At the corner of the street, it’s a good place to relax back. My favorite is No.4 ca phe, very fragrant taste
Coffee was very good! Wifi fast and easy to connect! Would go there again...
Very very noisy. Can't do anything here. Coffee was good but the fruit juice bad. Expensive. Toilet not very clean. Bad experience. Left the place with a headache.
Very good coffee, both traditional and western, brewed with espresso machine. The also serve many other beverages. Nice setting and warm comfortable interiors.
Coffees are great!... not so cheap but worth it. 😉
Coffee and drinks are nice but the settings are just as normal as other casual places; not up to Trung Nguyen upscale standards.

Wow! This was by far the worst coffee experience I’ve ever had. We ordered no. 2 and 3 iced with milk to go. After we paid they told us it would take 10-15 min - it took 20 minutes (if they’d told me this beforehand I would have gone someplace else). The place needs another barista and a second coffee machine. Once we got our coffees they were loaded! with sugar or just tasted super sweet. I tried to explain to the staff that I wanted both without sugar but little to no English hardly improved the situation. We ended up throwing both coffees away and going to another place.
Good place, but bad service. I ordered a coffee and wait for 30 minutes. They brought to me after 3 times reminder. Unfortunately, I have to leave for some businesses, so I cannot taste it.

I am always sceptical of places that advertise with being the number Nō 1 of XYZ, but once I had a taste of their traditional vietnamese coffee, oh my, it blew my mind. The only thing I could think of after the coffee was having more it! A truly unique taste.
Really bad experience here. Don’t come. Service is really bad
Good location, near road but quiet :) There is A little bit inconvience when i have to go up stair for rest room.

Yes the place deserves the hype indeed a calm place right next to busy streets BUT as heard the coffee isn’t that great Give it a try if you are free and have some time to actually have coffee or To be frank it’s a check in place to have ticked off your bucket list on the city

The food and coffee was extremely ordinary. The only good thing about this place was the location and its ambience.

Very nice interior with good vibe. Coffee was rather expensive for small (didn't order a small) cup, however it's worth it just for a nice air conditioned seat inside. They also have free green tea and water self service for all customers which is great.
Pretty efficient service, at times may get quite busy and noisy. The coffee products are of consistently good quality with special flavours characteristic of this brand.

This is probably one of, if not the first Trung Nguyen coffee in the city. It's nicely decorated on the exterior through to the interior, and has the colonial feel to it. They now do packaged sales, on top of the usual Starbucks-like made to order coffee. It's very premium feeling, and prices follow the feel too. That said, it's a very nice place to just grab a cuppa under the very warm weather.

Chain coffee house born and bred in Vietnam. Good quality coffee. Highly recommend everyone trying the legend coffee, which is the Vietnamese version of kopi luwak, which is civet coffee. My on,y reasoning for giving 4 stars for this location, is one time I visited, it was raining, and the staff would not allow me to sit outside, since they did not want to walk outside. original_text: Dịch vụ rất chuyên nghiệp, nhạc nền vừa đủ âm lượng, không gian rộng rãi, sang trọng, nước tự phục vụ khá ngon, món bò kho rất ngon
text: The service is very professional, the background music is loud enough, the space is spacious and luxurious, the self-service drinks are quite delicious, the braised beef dish is very delicious.

original_text: Quán cafe Trung Nguyên lớn nằm ngay góc Bùi Thị Xuân và Cách Mạng Tháng 8. Quán có bảo vệ giữ xe, bên trong rộng, bàn ghế bài trí gọn, thoải mái cho khách. Menu đủ các món cafe, ngoài ra còn có các món nước ép, sữa chua các loại ... giá cả hơi cao xíu. Thức uống ngon, cafe đậm đà, sữa chua béo ngọt ... điểm trừ là nhân viên gọi món thái độ không thân thiệt, mặt chù ụ
text: The large Trung Nguyen cafe is located right at the corner of Bui Thi Xuan and Cach Mang Thang 8. The shop has security parking, is spacious inside, and the tables and chairs are neatly arranged and comfortable for customers. The menu is full of coffee dishes, there are also juices, yogurts of all kinds... the prices are a bit high. Delicious drinks, rich coffee, sweet and fatty yogurt... the minus point is that the staff who ordered the food had an unfriendly attitude and a condescending face.

original_text: Hôm nay team mình có việc ra ngoài để làm việc, nên ghé cà phê Trung Nguyên ở đường Bùi Thị Xuân. Về vị trí, quán nằm ở góc ngã tư Cách Mạng Tháng 8 – Bùi Thị Xuân, là một vị trí cực kì thuận lợi để di chuyển. Bước vào quán, điểm làm mình ấn tượng đầu tiên không phải là décor, cũng không phải là không gian. Mà là … ghế. Bàn ghế ở đây phải gọi là sinh ra để dành cho bọn mình làm việc, cày deadline vậy. Mặt bàn rộng nên có thể để vừa 4 chiếc laptop. Chiều cao bàn cũng rất phù hợp, kết hợp với loại ghế sofa đơn dựa lưng, cực êm ái và dễ chịu. Thậm chí đôi lúc mệt, mình còn dựa lưng vào và chợp mắt một chút. Như những quán Trung Nguyên khác, menu nước của Trung Nguyên Bùi Thị Xuân rất đa dạng, từ nước trái cây cho đến soda. Mình highly recommend các bạn chọn món cà phê dừa, cà phê muối, chanh gừng sả hạt chia nhé. Trung Nguyên cũng có bán rất nhiều món ăn nữa. Hôm nay mình chọn 4 tô phở khô Gia Lai. Sợi phở cực kỳ mềm chứ không khô như những loại sợi hủ tiếu thông thường. Đặc biệt nhất là tương đen, tương ngọt ngon có thơm mùi đậu nành. Tương còn kết hợp với sa tế rất thơm nữa. Giá nước ở Trung Nguyên dao động từ 50 – 90k, còn đồ ăn khoảng 80k một món. Đây là mức giá rất phải chăng, nếu bạn so sánh với việc thuê một không gian làm việc co-working space ở những nơi khác. Hãy đến Trung Nguyên Bùi Thị Xuân và trải nghiệm không gian làm việc tuyệt vời này nhé!
text: Today my team had to go out to work, so we stopped by Trung Nguyen coffee on Bui Thi Xuan street.  Regarding location, the shop is located at the corner of Cach Mang Thang 8 - Bui Thi Xuan intersection, which is an extremely convenient location for moving. Entering the restaurant, the first thing that impressed me was not the décor, nor the space. Which is... chair. The tables and chairs here are said to be made for us to work and meet deadlines. The table surface is wide so it can fit 4 laptops. The table height is also very suitable, combined with a single-back sofa, extremely soft and comfortable. Even when I'm tired, I lean back and take a nap. Like other Trung Nguyen restaurants, Trung Nguyen Bui Thi Xuan's drink menu is very diverse, from juice to soda. I highly recommend you choose coconut coffee, salt coffee, lemon ginger lemongrass chia seeds. Trung Nguyen also sells many dishes. Today I chose 4 bowls of Gia Lai dry pho. The pho noodles are extremely soft and not dry like regular noodles. The most special is black soy sauce, a delicious sweet soy sauce with a fragrant aroma of soybeans. Soy sauce is also very fragrant when combined with satay. The price of water in Trung Nguyen ranges from 50 - 90k, while food is about 80k per dish. This is a very affordable price, if you compare it to renting a co-working space elsewhere. Come to Trung Nguyen Bui Thi Xuan and experience this wonderful working space!

original_text: Quán rộng, view công viên Tao Đàn, đồ uống tạm đc thôi, cà phê sữa nóng tại sao không pha máy mà lại để phin hông biết
text: The shop is spacious, has a view of Tao Dan park, the drinks are okay, hot milk coffee, why don't you brew it with a machine instead of leaving it on a filter?

original_text: 來到胡志明市後第一間品嚐的咖啡店，因爲在酒店旁邊，而且裝潢不錯，所以來之前就bookmark左了。後來發現是很出名的連鎖店，話雖如此，味道真的不錯，其實越南咖啡店每一家味道都很好。我在這裡喝了蛋咖啡，非常好喝，口感很好，很特別，非常建議試一次。 同埋我在超市買了Cafe Legend的即溶咖啡，也很好喝，可以買來試試。
text: This is the first coffee shop I tried after arriving in Ho Chi Minh City. Because it is next to the hotel and has a nice decoration, I bookmarked it before coming here. Later I found out that it is a very famous chain store. Having said that, the taste is really good. In fact, every Vietnamese coffee shop tastes very good. I drank egg coffee here. It was very delicious and tasted very special. I highly recommend giving it a try. I also bought Cafe Legend’s instant coffee in the supermarket. It’s also delicious. You can try it.

original_text: Không gian rộng rãi thoáng mát, giá nước cao hơn cà phê Katinat, Phúc Long. Ở đây bán đồ ăn sáng ngon tuyệt, giá cũng tương xứng với chất lượng. Vị trí đẹp, ngay góc đường Bùi Thị Xuân và Cách Mạng Tháng 8 nên khách du lịch khá là nhiều. Phục vụ nhanh, không có tiếp nước lọc cho khách, phải tự phục vụ
text: The space is spacious and airy, the price of water is higher than that of Katinat and Phuc Long coffee. Here they sell delicious breakfast food, the price is also commensurate with the quality. Nice location, right on the corner of Bui Thi Xuan and Cach Mang Thang 8 streets, so there are quite a lot of tourists. Fast service, no filtered water for customers, must serve yourself

original_text: Không gian quán rộng rãi, thoáng mát, vị trí ngay mặt tiền nên cũng dễ tìm Đồ ăn ở đây được làm rất chu đáo, ngon, hợp khẩu vị Nhân viên phục vụ nhiệt tình, chuyên nghiệp

Món kèm là kẹo cũng không phù hợp với người không thích ăn ngọt. Nó nên là bánh quy như bên DBP . phù hợp hơn với cafe. Không gian đẹp nhưng hơi chật hẹp và ồn ào.
text: The space is wonderful. Still true to Trung Nguyen. The egg coffee is very delicious, but somehow the flavor is different from the TN side in Dien Bien Phu. Candy as a side dish is also not suitable for people who don't like sweet foods. It should be biscuits like the DBP side. More suitable for coffee. The space is beautiful but a bit cramped and noisy.

original_text: Атмосферно, в заведении как минимум два этажа. Много деталей внутри можно ходить и рассматривать. You don’t need to go there specifically, but if you’re on the way, you can stop by.

It's still delicious, but the price is reasonable. I feel burdened by the cost of 50,000 won for 200 grams of grinds, so I go to the market and buy coffee beans.

text: It is a luxurious and quiet cafe. If you order and sit anywhere, they will bring it to you. It takes some time to get off Just pour it in well and drink it. There's something... it's a bitter and rich taste that I'm not used to.  Maybe it's because I'm used to the Highlands... I'm not sure.

original_text: Giá cao lắm nhưng mọi thứ khác ổn, vị trí thì đắc địa

original_text: Siamo ritornati qui la seconda volta e confermiamo l'impressione precedente: la musica proposta dal locale è solitamente una marcia o musica trionfale ed è ad un volume così alto che obbliga gli avventori a parlare molto forte con il risultato di un ambiente rumoroso che non aiuta a godersi il momento. Tra l'altro abbiamo preso lo stesso caffè del giorno prima ed il gusto era completamente diverso, molto più forte ed intenso. Non ritorneremo certamente. Tra l'altro la gente locale che frequenta questo posto è tutta vestita di vestiti firmati ma si comporta da contadino mettendo i piedi nel tavolino o usando il filo interdentale come se fosse in campagna! C'è molto di meglio in giro!
text: We returned here for the second time and we confirm the previous impression: the music played by the venue is usually a march or triumphal music and is at such a high volume that it forces the patrons to speak very loudly with the result of a noisy environment which does not help to enjoy the moment. Among other things, we drank the same coffee as the day before and the taste was completely different, much stronger and more intense. We certainly won't be returning. Among other things, the local people who frequent this place are all dressed in designer clothes but behave like farmers by putting their feet on the table or using dental floss as if they were in the countryside! There's so much better out there!

original_text: Thức ăn ngon, cafe Trung Nguyên thì không có gi nói quá tuyệt, không guan đẹp, giá hợp lý

original_text: Có mã giảm giá trên momo nên mình ghé thử. Cafe thơm, bày trí khá đẹp mắt nên đi kèm với giá không hề rẻ ^^. Với mình thì sẽ không ghé lại nếu không có mã giảm giá hoặc bạn bè rủ. Trừ 1* vì mình nghèo và mang lap vào làm việc mình thấy không hoàn toàn thoải mái. Ý kiến cá nhân thôi
text: There was a discount code on momo so I tried it out. The coffee is fragrant and beautifully decorated, so the price is not cheap ^^. For me, I won't stop by unless I have a discount code or a friend invites me. But I still recommend everyone to go if possible because the coffee is delicious and beautiful.  The restaurant space is also decorated quite beautifully. The table is a bit low compared to the chair, so it's a bit inconvenient to sit and work or study.  Minus 1* because I'm poor and I don't feel completely comfortable wearing a laptop to work. Just personal opinion

original_text: Quán cafe ngay ngã rẽ Bùi Thị Xuân giao Cách mạng tháng 8 nên view đẹp. Nước uống: cafe ngon, những ai có gu cafe đậm thì Trung Nguyên là 1 sự lựa chọn tốt. Nước khác giá hơi mắc ví dụ 1 quả dừa 50k, nhưng quán đầu tư mặt bằng nên giá này có thể chấp nhận được. Phục vụ: nhân viên dễ thương, thường xuyên dọn dẹp và châm nước ở khu vực chung. Tuy nhiên mình vừa đổ phin cafe vào li và muốn để chảy tiếp thì bạn nhân viên dọn dẹp luôn phin, làm mình nhớ đến nhân viên Haidilao không bao giờ để li trống. Nhà vệ sinh: sạch sẽ, có giấy, nước rửa tay đầy đủ, tuy nhiên hôm mình đi thì máy sấy bị hỏng. Gửi xe: miễn phí, có bảo vệ dắt xe giúp.
text: The cafe is right at the intersection of Bui Thi Xuan and August Revolution intersection, so the view is beautiful. Drinks: delicious coffee, for those who have a strong taste in coffee, Trung Nguyen is a good choice. In other countries, the price is a bit expensive, for example 1 coconut is 50k, but the shop has invested in space so this price is acceptable. Service: lovely staff, regularly cleaning and refilling water in the common area. However, I just poured the coffee filter into the cup and wanted to let it continue to flow, but the cleaning staff immediately poured the filter, reminding me of the Haidilao employee who never leaves the cup empty. Toilets: clean, with enough paper and hand sanitizer, however the day I went, the dryer was broken. Parking: free, there is a security guard to help guide the car.

original_text: Kopi legend No 1 Karena penasaran, saya mampir untuk sekedar mencoba. Vietnam terkenal dengan ekspor kopi robusta, bahkan no 2 terbesar di dunia. Meningat ini, saya semakin penasaran ingin mencoba. Pesanan saya dengan nama menu Legend Coffee.. harganya 150.000 Dong (uang vietnam), sekitar Rp 105.000 per cangkir. Menurut saya terlalu mahal jika secangkir kopi Robusta harganya di negara eksportir kopi terbesar no 2.. lihat gambar yang saya post. Hasil seduh kopi sekitar 30 ml kategori espresso. Dilengkapi dengan susu kental (saya tidak campur ini) dan secangkir es kristal.
text: Legendary coffee No. 1 Out of curiosity, I stopped by to just try. Vietnam is famous for its robusta coffee exports, in fact it is the second largest in the world. Remembering this, I was even more curious to try it. My order with the menu name Legend Coffee... the price is 150,000 Dong (Vietnamese money), around Rp. 105,000 per cup. In my opinion, it's too expensive for a cup of Robusta coffee in the second largest coffee exporting country... look at the picture I posted. The result of brewing coffee is around 30 ml of espresso category. Comes with condensed milk (I didn't mix this) and a cup of crystal ice.

original_text: Local muy bonito,moderno,limpio y elegante,gran variedad,muchos autóctonos,muy bueno cadé de coco,no vayas con prisas...

text: Spacious sitting space. 2 floors. Polite. I ordered Capuchino and Americano. Feeling good. Average price 60-70k/cup. Like Trung Nguyen's service. Opposite there is also another shop right at the beginning of Bui Thi Xuan. If you have free time, you will try it out.

text: The No.4 coffee recommended by the clerk is highly recommended! Although it is a little sour when you first enter your mouth, the aroma of coffee comes through later. Obviously Diandian is a latte but we are reluctant to add milk to it🤣  Most of the meals are quite delicious😋

original_text: Uống Cà phê sữa pha phin ở đây là tuyệt vời nhất đó với mình. Ko bị choáng như uống của highland và Starbuck. Giá 85k, thanh toán VNPay giảm tối đa ko quá 20k. Đối diện địa điểm này có món Bún Cá miền Tây. Món ăn ưa thích của tui ^.*
text: Drinking filter milk coffee here is the best for me. Doesn't get dizzy like drinking Highland and Starbucks. Price 85k, maximum discount with VNPay payment is no more than 20k. Opposite this location is Western Fish Noodles. My favorite dish ^.*

original_text: 밤에 숙소로 복귀하는 길에 들렀다. 고급스럽다는 느낌을 받은 건 우선 매우매우 시원하고, 자리에 앉으면 주문을 받으러 오신다..시원한 차같은 물과 함께! 계산은 후불! 흡연석과 금연석이 나뉘어져 있지만, 칸막이나 그런건 없고 그냥 바닥의 선이 그렇다 말해준다 ㅋㅋㅋ 핀커피로 먹었는데 기다림의 맛이 참 좋다! 영어가 되는 직원이 상주해 있어 편했다.
text: I stopped by on my way back to my accommodation at night. The first thing that gave me the feeling of luxury was that it was very, very refreshing, and when you sat down, they came to take your order… along with cool tea-like water! Pay later! There are separate smoking and non-smoking sections, but there are no partitions or anything like that, just a line on the floor. I had it as a pin coffee and it tastes so good while waiting! It was convenient to have staff who could speak English.

original_text: Trung Nguyên Legend Cafe là một trong những thương hiệu cà phê nổi tiếng tại Việt Nam. Ở số 2 Bùi Thị Xuân này, quán được bày trí khá tao nhã, không gian yên tĩnh, nhạc du dương. Có cả khu vực dành riêng cho người hút thuốc. Tuy vậy, mình vẫn chưa cảm thấy hài lòng với cách phục vụ của nhân viên, như thể họ chưa được đào tạo bài bản nên tác phong chưa được chuyên nghiệp và không chu đáo. Về thực đơn, các sản phẩm về cà phê thì khá ngon, riêng nước uống khác thì bình thường. Đồ ăn cũng không có gì nổi bật.
text: Trung Nguyen Legend Cafe is one of the famous coffee brands in Vietnam. At number 2 Bui Thi Xuan, the restaurant is decorated quite elegantly, has a quiet space, and melodious music. There is even a designated area for smokers.  However, I still do not feel satisfied with the staff's service, as if they have not been properly trained so their behavior is not professional and attentive.  Regarding the menu, the coffee products are quite delicious, but other drinks are normal. The food is also nothing outstanding.

original_text: Die Kaffees etc. sind verhältnismäßig teurer aber auch nett angerichtet und lecker. Jedoch hat die Zubereitung bei uns ca. 20min für 2 Kaffees gedauert. Unangenehmer empfand ich das Auftreten einiger anderen Gäste, welche ihre Bestellungen lautstark und aggressiv solange durch den gesamten Laden gerufen haben, bis es ihnen gebracht worden ist. Kein Wunder weshalb ich länger warten musste ;) Zusammenfassend: der Laden ist ok, jedoch mehr Schein als Sein. Es gibt auch qualitativ vergleichbare bzw. bessere Angebote in der Umgebung
text: The coffees etc. are relatively more expensive but are also nicely presented and tasty. However, it took us about 20 minutes to prepare two coffees. No wonder why I had to wait longer ;)  In summary: the store is ok, but more appearance than reality. There are also offers of comparable or better quality in the area

text: The place is nice, but the quality of service is deplorable. More than 20 minutes of waiting before receiving 4 fruit juices, each delivered 5 minutes apart!!! When paying the bill, she made no discount, to compensate for the damage to my clothes, making us understand that she was simply limiting herself to replacing the glass that she spilled on me, out of pure clumsiness. Furthermore, going to the counter, I asked for the business card of this "establishment", and this was very clearly and clearly refused to me, for fear of negative reviews on the Internet...! This is the height of irresponsibility! Note that this waitress, really very clumsy, also spilled a second glass on the floor, near our table, 10 minutes after she spilled this passion fruit juice on my clothes...! The cleaning by my hotel cost me 110,000 dong. I therefore cannot recommend frequenting such a café, which is incapable of assuming the slightest of its responsibilities.
